OL,3,CState pension errors 'could be
OL,4,Cvirtually impossible to fix if records
OL,5,Cdeleted'
OL,7,FA freedom of information (FOI)
OL,8,Fresponse received by Sir Steve, who
OL,9,Fhad requested information from the
OL,10,FDWP, said that in 2021 the department
OL,11,Fput a temporary pause on deletions, as
OL,12,Fpart of the major correction exercise
OL,13,Fon underpaid pensions to married
OL,14,Fwomen, widows and the over-80s.
OL,16,FSir Steve said that as pension records
OL,17,Fare normally deleted four years after
OL,18,Fsomeone dies, there is a risk that
OL,19,Frecords all the way back to 2017 could
OL,20,Feventually be wiped, making it harder
OL,21,Ffor families to receive justice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
